I use detergent and water in a half keg on the big cajun-
cooker/homebrew burner. Boil until they're clean.

 -Harry in Fresno

> If you have the time, simply soak them in hot water and soap.
> 
> Otherwise, use solvents made for degreasing
> 
> You don't need high temp paint, but if you go to bare metal you really
> need to degrease well, prime, and paint to get the paint to stick.  Try to
> preserve the original paint if you can!
> 
> George
